Privacy Policy for MeetScapes
Effective Date: 11/15/2024

At MeetScapes, we respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and safeguard your data when you access and use the MeetScapes app.

1. Information We Collect

We do not collect any personally identifiable information (PII) when you use the MeetScapes app unless explicitly stated.

However, when using MeetScapes through GitHub Pages, the following data may be collected automatically:

Usage Data: We may collect information on how you interact with the app, including page views, interactions, and the frequency of use.

Cookies: The app may use cookies to enhance user experience by remembering your preferences and settings.

2. How We Use Your Information

The information collected is used solely for:

Improving and enhancing the appâ€™s functionality.

Understanding how users interact with the app to provide better user experiences.

Ensuring the app functions correctly and securely.

3. Data Sharing

We do not share or sell any personal data to third parties. We do not use third-party analytics or advertising services. The only data shared will be in cases of legal requirements or if we are compelled by law to disclose specific information.

4. Security

We are committed to ensuring that your information is secure. We implement a variety of security measures to protect your personal data, including:

HTTPS encryption: All data transmitted between the app and your browser is encrypted using HTTPS.

Regular security audits: We conduct regular security reviews to detect vulnerabilities and improve app safety.

5. Cookies

The MeetScapes website may use cookies to store user preferences and enhance the user experience. A cookie is a small file placed on your device, which helps us improve the functionality and performance of the app. You can control cookie settings through your browser.

6. Third-Party Links

The MeetScapes app may contain links to third-party websites. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these third-party sites. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of any third-party websites you visit.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We reserve the right to update or modify this Privacy Policy at any time. If we make changes, we will update the "Effective Date" at the top of this policy. We encourage you to review this page periodically for any updates.

8. Contact Information

If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or the practices of MeetScapes, please contact us at:

